He finished the season as the year-end No. 1 for the fourth year in a row, demonstrating his dominance, and during these four years he won 11 Grand Slam singles titles. After his phenomenal triple Grand Slam season yet again, Federer became the only player in history to win three majors in a year for three years (2004, 2006, 2007).[71][72][73][74] It was the third consecutive season that Federer held the No. 1 ranking for all 52 weeks of the year.[49]
